Slovakiaâ€™s Tatra Mountain Resort AS
has agreed to operate Spindlerov Mlyn ski resort in the
neighboring  Czech Republic  for 20 years,  Hospodarske Noviny 
reported, citing TMR Chairman Bohus Hlavaty.  TMR will pay 1.8 million euros ($2.3 million) a year to
operate the resort and has an option to extend the lease for
another 20 years, the newspaper said. The Slovak company also
agreed to invest 32.2 million euros in upgrading the facilities,
